# ISS-562 - scripted test for the sge-build BROWSER packaging task.
# Exercises SgePackaging.sgePackageBrowser (browser HTML/manifest generation)
# against a fresh hello-world project built on the locally-published sge-build
# plugin. The fullLinkJS step is bypassed by overriding sgeJsOutputDir to a stub
# directory containing a fake main.js (see build.sbt) — so the real HTML/copy/
# manifest logic runs without invoking the Scala.js linker.

# Assert the package contents via the custom checkBrowserPackage task. This task
# depends on (and therefore runs) game.js(...) / sgePackageBrowser, so the browser
# packaging task is exercised here.
#   - index.html exists + contains the title, the <script src="main.js"> tag,
#     and the Loading/app-name text
#   - main.js was copied into the output
#   - assets/assets.txt exists + contains the asset entries
# This is the assertion the CANARY regression must trip.
> checkBrowserPackage

# The browser package outputs must physically exist on disk (JS axis target is
# game/target/js-3 for the projectMatrix JS axis).
$ exists game/target/js-3/sge-browser/hello-sge-browser/index.html
$ exists game/target/js-3/sge-browser/hello-sge-browser/main.js
$ exists game/target/js-3/sge-browser/hello-sge-browser/assets/assets.txt
